"`separate\" and the microstructure is sufficiently fine with\nrespect to the length scale of the domain $\\omega_i$ it is shown that\nhomogenization theory can be used to construct local approximation spaces with\nexponentially decreasing error in the pre-asymtotic regime.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 18 Apr 2010 17:30:49 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 28 Nov 2010 21:32:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2010-11-30"}
